sql:
SELECT DISTINCT i.instructor_id, i.instructor_name
FROM instructors AS i
JOIN course_instructors AS ci ON i.instructor_id = ci.instructor_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'primary department head' refers to the department head with ID 1;
- 'educators' and 'instructors' are synonymous terms referring to teachers;
- 'classes' and 'courses' are used interchangeably to refer to the subjects taught.

